Description: Fragment of a seal-impression of clay, the rear shows traces of several strings, maybe remains of a bolt, the front shows parts of a larger impression of which only parts are preserved, two circumferential lines, perpendicular to them an oval line like a cartouche, inside a rounded sing is visible, rest not very clear.
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 231)
